✅ COPPA Notice (Original / Ready to Use)

Children’s Privacy (COPPA Notice)
This software is built for a general audience and is not specifically designed for children under 13.

Telepathic Wind Robot — Cyber-Mystic Analyzer does not intentionally collect, store, transmit, or process personal information from children under 13 (as defined by COPPA).

Current behavior of the software:

No account creation required

No requests for name, email, or personal identifiers

Microphone input is used only for live, local, in-browser visualization

No audio is recorded, saved, uploaded, or shared

Audio signals exist only temporarily in memory and are discarded immediately

If you are under 13:
Do not enable the microphone or use microphone-based features.

If you are a parent/guardian and believe a child used this software in a way that could involve personal information:
Stop using the software immediately. The current design does not retain user data.

General-purpose statement:
This software is intended for experimentation and visualization and is not a recording or monitoring tool.

⚠️ Technical warning (COPPA trigger list)

If the project later adds any of the following, COPPA review and disclosures must be revisited:

Saving audio (files or recordings)

Storing frequency/analysis data tied to sessions or identities

User accounts, profiles, or logins

Analytics tied to IP/device identifiers

Cloud logging or remote storage

“Share” / export / social publishing features that transmit user-related data

Current safety posture:

Processing is local-only

Data is not persisted

Nothing is transmitted off-device

