Expanded compliance research notes for the Telepathic Immortal project, including privacy, disclosures, and best-practice alignment (non-exhaustive, ongoing).

Frameworks / areas reviewed and mapped into project documentation:

— U.S. Federal Privacy & Consumer Protection —

Federal Trade Commission (FTC) concepts reviewed:

Privacy and data security guidance

“Truth in advertising” as it applies to software claims and user-facing statements

Clear-and-conspicuous disclosure expectations

Consent clarity and avoidance of deceptive UI practices (dark-pattern risk)

Accuracy in describing microphone/audio behavior (recording vs. visualization vs. transmission)

COPPA (Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act) considerations reviewed:

General-audience vs. child-directed positioning

What “collection” means and what counts as personal information

Real-time processing vs. storage/retention concerns

Ensuring disclosures match actual technical behavior

Avoiding identity-linked audio or analytics

State audio consent model (working reference list; verify statutes before making formal legal claims):

